{{Redirect|BitTorrent client|the client created by [[Bram Cohen]]|BitTorrent (software)}}
{{List dispute|date=June 2011}}
{{Refimprove|date=September 2009}}
A '''BitTorrent client''' is a [[computer program]] that manages [[uploading and downloading|downloads and uploads]] using the [[BitTorrent (protocol)|BitTorrent protocol]].

The first [[client (computing)|client]], known as [[BitTorrent (software)|BitTorrent]], was created by [[Bram Cohen]], in October 2002.

Many subsequent clients have been at least partially based on it. Not all clients were originally built for BitTorrent, having added support for the protocol later on. There have been attempts to package [[malware]] as BitTorrent clients, probably due to the availability of many legitimate clients and users' willingness to try new ones.

The following tables compare general and technical information for a number of applications supporting the [[BitTorrent (protocol)|BitTorrent protocol]]. They are neither all-inclusive nor necessarily up to date.

== Applications ==
''Note: Clients in blue are no longer in development.''

