=== Features I ===

{| style="font-size: 85%; text-align: center;" class="wikitable sortable"
|-
! BitTorrent client
! [[Magnet URI]]
! [[Super-seeding]]
! [[BitTorrent tracker|Embedded tracker]]
! [[Universal Plug and Play|UPnP]]<ref name="upnp">Automatically configure port forwarding (requires [[Router (computing)|Router]] with [[Universal Plug and Play|UPnP]] support)</ref>
! [[NAT Port Mapping Protocol]]
! [[NAT traversal]]<ref name="udp_nat">Many clients claim to support this, but just uPnP calls for opening a TCP port is not effective and disabled by factory default in most new hardware. "UDP NAT Traversal" is the proper working solution, supported by just a few.</ref>
! [[Distributed hash table|DHT]]<ref name="dht">DHT permits use of trackerless torrents (with supporting clients) to resume normal torrents when their tracker is down. However, some trackers that register their users for keeping tabs on fair usage (such as a ratio of bytes downloaded to uploaded) may not reliably measure and update usage for users employing DHT.</ref>
! [[Peer exchange]]
! [[BitTorrent protocol encryption|Encryption]]
! [[UDP tracker]]
! [[Local Peer Discovery|LPD]]
! [[Proxy]]
